<body>

<h1>📡 Wiom Netbox Physical Verification Tool</h1>
<p class="meta">
  <strong>Project:</strong> Prompt Wars 2 — Problem #1 &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  <strong>Date:</strong> March 18, 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  <strong>Repo:</strong> https://github.com/bulkentropy/wiom-audit-tool &nbsp;|&nbsp;
  <strong>Status:</strong> <span class="badge-yellow">Deploying to Render</span>
</p>

<hr>

<h2>1. Problem Statement</h2>
<p>
  Wiom distributes Netbox routers to partners in batches. Partners acknowledge receipt <strong>by count, not by device ID</strong>, creating a traceability gap from day one. Devices move through states (at Wiom → at partner → at customer → recovered → returned), but grey zones exist: unlogged pickups, expired tickets, cross-window transfers.
</p>
<p>
  Wiom has device-level dispatch data but no scalable way to verify physical possession without expensive field visits. This tool solves that with a <strong>zero-field-visit, partner-driven digital stocktake</strong> — hosted on the web and shareable with judges.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>2. Solution Overview</h2>
<p>A hosted two-sided web tool with two entry points:</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Portal</th><th>Who Uses It</th><th>URL</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Ops Portal</strong></td><td>Wiom internal team</td><td>/ops</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Partner Portal</strong></td><td>Field partners (mobile + PC)</td><td>/partner</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Technology Stack</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js + Express</li>
  <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS — no framework (fast on basic Android, works on PC)</li>
  <li><strong>Barcode scanning:</strong> ZXing-js (browser camera, no app install needed)</li>
  <li><strong>Auth:</strong> express-session with hardcoded credentials</li>
  <li><strong>Data:</strong> CSV files loaded at startup into memory</li>
  <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Render.com free tier</li>
</ul>

<hr>

