<hr>

<h2>4. Data Model</h2>
<h3>Input CSV Files</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>File</th><th>Columns</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td>dispatch.csv</td><td>partner_id, device_id, mac_id, dispatch_date, batch_id</td><td>Every device dispatched to every partner</td></tr>
  <tr><td>device_states.csv</td><td>device_id, current_state</td><td>Current lifecycle state of each device</td></tr>
  <tr><td>pickup_tickets.csv</td><td>ticket_id, device_id, partner_id, status, created_at, closed_at</td><td>Customer pickup/return tickets</td></tr>
  <tr><td>partners.csv</td><td>partner_id, partner_name, username, pin, operating_windows</td><td>Partner master data + credentials</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Device States</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>State</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
  <tr><td>at_wiom</td><td>Returned to warehouse</td></tr>
  <tr><td>at_partner</td><td>With partner (expected)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>at_customer</td><td>Deployed to end customer</td></tr>
  <tr><td>unknown</td><td>Location unclear</td></tr>
  <tr><td>at_partner_recovered_unlogged</td><td>Auto-corrected: found with partner, system hadn't recorded return</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Expected Accountability Formula</h3>
<div class="section-box">
  <p><strong>Expected at partner =</strong></p>
  <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;All devices dispatched to partner</p>
  <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>MINUS</strong> devices returned to warehouse (state: at_wiom)</p>
  <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>MINUS</strong> devices on active customer plans (state: at_customer + active ticket)</p>
  <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>MINUS</strong> devices with completed pickup tickets (marked recovered)</p>
</div>

<h3>Audit Result Categories</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Category</th><th>Condition</th></tr>
  <tr><td>✅ Verified</td><td>On expected list + scanned by partner</td></tr>
  <tr><td>❌ Missing</td><td>On expected list + NOT scanned</td></tr>
  <tr><td>⚠️ Unexpected</td><td>Scanned but NOT on expected list — lifecycle check runs automatically</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🔄 State Corrected</td><td>Unexpected device with resolvable lifecycle — state auto-updated in system</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🚨 Unauthorized</td><td>Scanned device dispatched to a different partner</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>

<h2>5. Project File Structure</h2>
<div class="code-block">
/wiom-audit-tool
  /backend
    server.js           ← Express server, routes, session auth
    reconcile.js        ← Expected inventory computation
    csvLoader.js        ← Parse all CSVs into memory on startup
    stateCorrector.js   ← Grey zone lifecycle resolution
    mockDataGen.js      ← Generates mock CSVs (run once or at deploy)
  /frontend
    /ops
      login.html        ← Ops login page
      index.html        ← Dataset info + partner credentials
      dashboard.html    ← Live audit status table + download reports
      partner-detail.html  ← Device-level view per partner
    /partner
      login.html        ← Partner login (username + PIN keypad)
      welcome.html      ← Instructions + expected device count
      audit.html        ← Live scan/checklist interface
      complete.html     ← Summary + submit
    /css
      ops.css           ← Clean desktop layout
      partner.css       ← Mobile-first, large touch targets
  /data
    dispatch.csv
    device_states.csv
    pickup_tickets.csv
    partners.csv
  package.json
  render.yaml           ← Render.com deployment config
  progress.md           ← This project's task tracker
</div>

