<h2>8. Deployment</h2>

<h3>Run Locally</h3>
<div class="code-block">
cd C:\Users\ajink\wiom-audit-tool

# Note: ports 3000 and 3001 are occupied on this machine
PORT=4000 node backend/server.js

# Ops:     http://localhost:4000/ops
# Partner: http://localhost:4000/partner
</div>

<h3>Deploy to Render.com</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Repo is already pushed: https://github.com/bulkentropy/wiom-audit-tool</li>
  <li>Go to <strong>render.com</strong> → New + → Web Service → Connect <code>bulkentropy/wiom-audit-tool</code></li>
  <li>Render auto-reads <code>render.yaml</code>:
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Build:</strong> <code>npm install &amp;&amp; node backend/mockDataGen.js</code></li>
      <li><strong>Start:</strong> <code>node backend/server.js</code></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Click <strong>Deploy</strong> — takes ~2 minutes</li>
  <li>Live URLs will be <code>https://wiom-audit.onrender.com/ops</code> and <code>/partner</code></li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2>9. Bugs Found and Fixed</h2>

<h3>Bug 1 — Pages not loading (/ops and /partner redirecting wrongly)</h3>
<p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Navigating to /ops showed the home page (index.html) instead of the login page.</p>
<p><strong>Root cause:</strong> <code>express.static</code> middleware was registered before route handlers. When a request came in for <code>/ops</code>, Express static saw it as a directory (<code>frontend/ops/</code>) and redirected to <code>/ops/</code> which served <code>index.html</code> directly — bypassing the login route entirely.</p>
<p><strong>Fix:</strong> Moved explicit GET route declarations before <code>express.static()</code>, and added <code>{ redirect: false }</code> to prevent directory redirects.</p>
<p><strong>Commit:</strong> dd00f21</p>

<h3>Bug 2 — "Could not load data" + continuous refresh loop on ops home</h3>
<p><strong>Symptom:</strong> After login, the ops home page showed "Loading..." then "Could not load data." and kept refreshing in a loop.</p>
<p><strong>Root cause:</strong> The auth check (<code>fetch('/api/ops/me')</code>) and data fetch (<code>fetch('/api/ops/summary')</code>) fired in parallel. If the session had expired (e.g. after a server restart clearing in-memory sessions), both requests got 401. The summary 401 caused "Could not load data.", the auth check triggered a redirect to /ops (login), the user logged in, went back to /ops/home — and the same race condition repeated.</p>
<p><strong>Fix:</strong> Rewrote all ops page scripts to <code>await</code> the auth check before fetching any data. If auth fails, redirect happens cleanly with no error flicker. Applied to index.html, dashboard.html, and partner-detail.html.</p>
<p><strong>Commit:</strong> ab0fe00</p>

<hr>

<h2>10. Known Limitations</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Item</th><th>Impact</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
  <tr>
    <td>In-memory sessions</td>
    <td>Server restart clears all sessions</td>
    <td>Acceptable for hackathon demo. Production would use Redis or DB-backed sessions.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Barcode scanning on iOS Safari (HTTP)</td>
    <td>Camera blocked on HTTP</td>
    <td>Works on Render deploy (HTTPS). Manual entry fallback always available.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>CSV upload mode</td>
    <td>UI exists but backend not wired</td>
    <td>Demo mode (pre-loaded data) covers all judge-facing scenarios.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>No persistent database</td>
    <td>Audit state lost on restart</td>
    <td>Fine for demo. Would need SQLite or Postgres for production.</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<hr>

<h2>11. API Reference</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Method</th><th>Endpoint</th><th>Auth</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/ops/login</td><td>—</td><td>{ username, password }</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ops/me</td><td>Ops</td><td>Check session validity</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ops/summary</td><td>Ops</td><td>All partners + audit status</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ops/partner/:id</td><td>Ops</td><td>Device-level detail for one partner</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ops/report/full</td><td>Ops</td><td>Full reconciliation CSV download</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ops/report/corrections</td><td>Ops</td><td>State corrections CSV download</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/ops/report/missing</td><td>Ops</td><td>Missing devices CSV download</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/partner/login</td><td>—</td><td>{ username, pin }</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/partner/me</td><td>Partner</td><td>Check session + get partner info</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/partner/expected</td><td>Partner</td><td>Expected device list for logged-in partner</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/partner/scan</td><td>Partner</td><td>{ device_id } — scan a device, returns category</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/partner/summary</td><td>Partner</td><td>Verified / missing / unexpected counts</td></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/partner/submit</td><td>Partner</td><td>Lock and submit the audit</td></tr>
</table>

